 229     /**                                                                                                  
 230      * Restore launcher configuration from the restored data stream.                                     
 231      *                                                                                                   
 232      * <P>Keys may arrive in any order.                                                                  
 233      *                                                                                                   
 234      * @param data the key/value pair from the server                                                    
 235      */                                                                                                  
 236     @Override                                                                                            
 237     public void restoreEntity(BackupDataInputStream data) {                                              
 238         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "restoreEntity");                                                        
 239         byte[] buffer = new byte[512];                                                                   
 240             String backupKey = data.getKey();                                                            
 241             int dataSize = data.size();                                                                  
 242             if (buffer.length < dataSize) {                                                              
 243                 buffer = new byte[dataSize];                                                             
 244             }                                                                                            
 245             Key key = null;                                                                              
 246         int bytesRead = 0;                                                                               
 247         try {                                                                                            
 248             bytesRead = data.read(buffer, 0, dataSize);                                                  
 249             if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "read " + bytesRead + " of " + dataSize + " available");               
 250         } catch (IOException e) {                                                                        
 251             Log.e(TAG, "failed to read entity from restore data", e);                                    
 252         }                                                                                                
 253         try {                                                                                            
 254             key = backupKeyToKey(backupKey);                                                             
 255             mKeys.add(key);                                                                              
 256             switch (key.type) {                                                                          
 257                 case Key.FAVORITE:                                                                       
 258                     restoreFavorite(key, buffer, dataSize, mKeys);                                       
 259                     break;                                                                               
 260                                                                                                          
 261                 case Key.SCREEN:                                                                         
 262                     restoreScreen(key, buffer, dataSize, mKeys);                                         
 263                     break;                                                                               
 264                                                                                                          
 265                 case Key.ICON:                                                                           
 266                     restoreIcon(key, buffer, dataSize, mKeys);                                           
 267                     break;                                                                               
 268                                                                                                          
 269                 case Key.WIDGET:                                                                         
 270                     restoreWidget(key, buffer, dataSize, mKeys);                                         
 271                     break;                                                                               
 272                                                                                                          
 273                 default:                                                                                 
 274                     Log.w(TAG, "unknown restore entity type: " + key.type);                              
 275                     break;                                                                               
 276             }                                                                                            
 277         } catch (KeyParsingException e) {                                                                
 278             Log.w(TAG, "ignoring unparsable backup key: " + backupKey);                                  
 279         }                                                                                                
 280                                                                                                          
 281     }

 314     /**                                                                                                  
 315      * Write all modified favorites to the data stream.                                                  
 316      *                                                                                                   
 317      *                                                                                                   
 318      * @param in notes from last backup                                                                  
 319      * @param data output stream for key/value pairs                                                     
 320      * @param out notes about this backup                                                                
 321      * @param keys keys to mark as clean in the notes for next backup                                    
 322      * @throws IOException                                                                               
 323      */                                                                                                  
 324     private void backupFavorites(Journal in, BackupDataOutput data, Journal out,                         
 325             ArrayList<Key> keys)                                                                         
 326             throws IOException {                                                                         
 327         // read the old ID set                                                                           
 328         Set<String> savedIds = getSavedIdsByType(Key.FAVORITE, in);                                      
 329         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "favorite savedIds.size()=" + savedIds.size());                            
 330                                                                                                          
 331         // persist things that have changed since the last backup                                        
 332         ContentResolver cr = mContext.getContentResolver();                                              
 333         // Don't backup apps in other profiles for now.                                                  
 334         Cursor cursor = cr.query(Favorites.CONTENT_URI, FAVORITE_PROJECTION,                             
 335                 getUserSelectionArg(), null, null);                                                      
 336         Set<String> currentIds = new HashSet<String>(cursor.getCount());                                 
 337         try {                                                                                            
 338             cursor.moveToPosition(-1);                                                                   
 339             while(cursor.moveToNext()) {                                                                 
 340                 final long id = cursor.getLong(ID_INDEX);                                                
 341                 final long updateTime = cursor.getLong(ID_MODIFIED);                                     
 342                 Key key = getKey(Key.FAVORITE, id);                                                      
 343                 keys.add(key);                                                                           
 344                 final String backupKey = keyToBackupKey(key);                                            
 345                 currentIds.add(backupKey);                                                               
 346                 if (!savedIds.contains(backupKey) || updateTime >= in.t) {                               
 347                     byte[] blob = packFavorite(cursor);                                                  
 348                     writeRowToBackup(key, blob, out, data);                                              
 349                 } else {                                                                                 
 350                     if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "favorite " + id + " was too old: " + updateTime);           
 351                 }                                                                                        
 352             }                                                                                            
 353         } finally {                                                                                      
 354             cursor.close();                                                                              
 355         }                                                                                                
 356         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "favorite currentIds.size()=" + currentIds.size());                        
 357                                                                                                          
 358         // these IDs must have been deleted                                                              
 359         savedIds.removeAll(currentIds);                                                                  
 360         out.rows += removeDeletedKeysFromBackup(savedIds, data);                                         
 361     }

 363     /**                                                                                                  
 364      * Read a favorite from the stream.                                                                  
 365      *                                                                                                   
 366      * <P>Keys arrive in any order, so screens and containers may not exist yet.                         
 367      *                                                                                                   
 368      * @param key identifier for the row                                                                 
 369      * @param buffer the serialized proto from the stream, may be larger than dataSize                   
 370      * @param dataSize the size of the proto from the stream                                             
 371      * @param keys keys to mark as clean in the notes for next backup                                    
 372      */                                                                                                  
 373     private void restoreFavorite(Key key, byte[] buffer, int dataSize, ArrayList<Key> keys) {            
 374         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "unpacking favorite " + key.id);                                         
 375         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "read (" + buffer.length + "): " +                                         
 376                 Base64.encodeToString(buffer, 0, dataSize, Base64.NO_WRAP));                             
 377                                                                                                          
 378         if (!mRestoreEnabled) {                                                                          
 379             if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "restore not enabled: skipping database mutation");                  
 380             return;                                                                                      
 381         }                                                                                                
 382                                                                                                          
 383         try {                                                                                            
 384             ContentResolver cr = mContext.getContentResolver();                                          
 385             ContentValues values = unpackFavorite(buffer, 0, dataSize);                                  
 386             cr.insert(Favorites.CONTENT_URI_NO_NOTIFICATION, values);                                    
 387         } catch (InvalidProtocolBufferNanoException e) {                                                 
 388             Log.e(TAG, "failed to decode favorite", e);                                                  
 389         }                                                                                                
 390     }

 471     /**

 497         // Don't backup apps in other profiles for now.                                                  
 498         int startRows = out.rows;                                                                        
 499         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "starting here: " + startRows);                                            
 500                                                                                                          
 501         String where = "(" + Favorites.ITEM_TYPE + "=" + Favorites.ITEM_TYPE_APPLICATION + " OR " +      
 502                 Favorites.ITEM_TYPE + "=" + Favorites.ITEM_TYPE_SHORTCUT + ") AND " +                    
 503                 getUserSelectionArg();                                                                   
 504         Cursor cursor = cr.query(Favorites.CONTENT_URI, FAVORITE_PROJECTION,                             
 505                 where, null, null);                                                                      
 506         Set<String> currentIds = new HashSet<String>(cursor.getCount());                                 
 507         try {                                                                                            
 508             cursor.moveToPosition(-1);                                                                   
 509             while(cursor.moveToNext()) {                                                                 
 510                 final long id = cursor.getLong(ID_INDEX);                                                
 511                 final String intentDescription = cursor.getString(INTENT_INDEX);                         
 512                 try {                                                                                    
 513                     Intent intent = Intent.parseUri(intentDescription, 0);                               
 514                     ComponentName cn = intent.getComponent();                                            
 515                     Key key = null;                                                                      
 516                     String backupKey = null;                                                             
 517                     if (cn != null) {                                                                    
 518                         key = getKey(Key.ICON, cn.flattenToShortString());                               
 519                         backupKey = keyToBackupKey(key);                                                 
 520                         currentIds.add(backupKey);                                                       
 521                     } else {                                                                             
 522                         Log.w(TAG, "empty intent on application favorite: " + id);                       
 523                     }                                                                                    
 524                     if (savedIds.contains(backupKey)) {                                                  
 525                         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "already saved icon " + backupKey);                      
 526                                                                                                          
 527                         // remember that we already backed this up previously                            
 528                         keys.add(key);                                                                   
 529                     } else if (backupKey != null) {                                                      
 530                         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "I can count this high: " + out.rows);                     
 531                         if ((out.rows - startRows) < MAX_ICONS_PER_PASS) {                               
 532                             if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "saving icon " + backupKey);                         
 533                             Bitmap icon = mIconCache.getIcon(intent, myUserHandle);                      
 534                             keys.add(key);                                                               
 535                             if (icon != null && !mIconCache.isDefaultIcon(icon, myUserHandle)) {         
 536                                 byte[] blob = packIcon(dpi, icon);                                       
 537                                 writeRowToBackup(key, blob, out, data);                                  
 538                             }                                                                            
 539                         } else {                                                                         
 540                             if (VERBOSE) Log.d(TAG, "deferring icon backup " + backupKey);               
 541                             // too many icons for this pass, request another.                            
 542                             dataChanged();                                                               
 543                         }                                                                                
 544                     }                                                                                    
 545                 } catch (URISyntaxException e) {                                                         
 546                     Log.e(TAG, "invalid URI on application favorite: " + id);                            
 547                 } catch (IOException e) {                                                                
 548                     Log.e(TAG, "unable to save application icon for favorite: " + id);                   
 549                 }                                                                                        
 550                                                                                                          
 551             }                                                                                            
 552         } finally {                                                                                      
 553             cursor.close();                                                                              
 554         }                                                                                                
 555         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "icon currentIds.size()=" + currentIds.size());                            
 556                                                                                                          
 557         // these IDs must have been deleted                                                              
 558         savedIds.removeAll(currentIds);                                                                  
 559         out.rows += removeDeletedKeysFromBackup(savedIds, data);                                         
 560     }

 562     /**                                                                                                  
 563      * Read an icon from the stream.                                                                     
 564      *                                                                                                   
 565      * <P>Keys arrive in any order, so shortcuts that use this icon may already exist.                   
 566      *                                                                                                   
 567      * @param key identifier for the row                                                                 
 568      * @param buffer the serialized proto from the stream, may be larger than dataSize                   
 569      * @param dataSize the size of the proto from the stream                                             
 570      * @param keys keys to mark as clean in the notes for next backup                                    
 571      */                                                                                                  
 572     private void restoreIcon(Key key, byte[] buffer, int dataSize, ArrayList<Key> keys) {                
 573         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "unpacking icon " + key.id);                                             
 574         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "read (" + buffer.length + "): " +                                         
 575                 Base64.encodeToString(buffer, 0, dataSize, Base64.NO_WRAP));                             
 576                                                                                                          
 577         try {                                                                                            
 578             Resource res = unpackIcon(buffer, 0, dataSize);                                              
 579             if (DEBUG) {                                                                                 
 580                 Log.d(TAG, "unpacked " + res.dpi + " dpi icon");                                         
 581             }                                                                                            
 582             if (DEBUG_PAYLOAD) {                                                                         
 583                 Log.d(TAG, "read " +                                                                     
 584                         Base64.encodeToString(res.data, 0, res.data.length,                              
 585                                 Base64.NO_WRAP));                                                        
 586             }                                                                                            
 587             Bitmap icon = BitmapFactory.decodeByteArray(res.data, 0, res.data.length);                   
 588             if (icon == null) {                                                                          
 589                 Log.w(TAG, "failed to unpack icon for " + key.name);                                     
 590             }                                                                                            
 591                                                                                                          
 592             if (!mRestoreEnabled) {                                                                      
 593                 if (VERBOSE) {                                                                           
 594                     Log.v(TAG, "restore not enabled: skipping database mutation");                       
 595                 }                                                                                        
 596                 return;                                                                                  
 597             } else {                                                                                     
 598                 if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "saving restored icon as: " + key.name);                         
 599                 IconCache.preloadIcon(mContext, ComponentName.unflattenFromString(key.name),             
 600                         icon, res.dpi);                                                                  
 601             }                                                                                            
 602         } catch (IOException e) {                                                                        
 603             Log.d(TAG, "failed to save restored icon for: " + key.name, e);                              
 604         }                                                                                                
 605     }

 607     /**                                                                                                  
 608      * Write all the static widget resources we need to render placeholders                              
 609      * for a package that is not installed.                                                              
 610      *                                                                                                   
 611      * @param in notes from last backup                                                                  
 612      * @param data output stream for key/value pairs                                                     
 613      * @param out notes about this backup                                                                
 614      * @param keys keys to mark as clean in the notes for next backup                                    
 615      * @throws IOException                                                                               
 616      */                                                                                                  
 617     private void backupWidgets(Journal in, BackupDataOutput data, Journal out,                           
 618             ArrayList<Key> keys) throws IOException {                                                    
 619         // persist static widget info that hasn't been persisted yet                                     
 620         final LauncherAppState appState = LauncherAppState.getInstanceNoCreate();                        
 621         if (appState == null || !initializeIconCache()) {                                                
 622             Log.w(TAG, "Failed to get icon cache during restore");                                       
 623             return;                                                                                      
 624         }                                                                                                
 625         final ContentResolver cr = mContext.getContentResolver();                                        
 626         final WidgetPreviewLoader previewLoader = new WidgetPreviewLoader(mContext);                     
 627         final PagedViewCellLayout widgetSpacingLayout = new PagedViewCellLayout(mContext);               
 628         final int dpi = mContext.getResources().getDisplayMetrics().densityDpi;                          
 629         final DeviceProfile profile = appState.getDynamicGrid().getDeviceProfile();                      
 630         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "cellWidthPx: " + profile.cellWidthPx);                                    
 631                                                                                                          
 632         // read the old ID set                                                                           
 633         Set<String> savedIds = getSavedIdsByType(Key.WIDGET, in);                                        
 634         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "widgets savedIds.size()=" + savedIds.size());                             
 635                                                                                                          
 636         int startRows = out.rows;                                                                        
 637         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "starting here: " + startRows);                                            
 638         String where = Favorites.ITEM_TYPE + "=" + Favorites.ITEM_TYPE_APPWIDGET + " AND "               
 639                 + getUserSelectionArg();                                                                 
 640         Cursor cursor = cr.query(Favorites.CONTENT_URI, FAVORITE_PROJECTION,                             
 641                 where, null, null);                                                                      
 642         Set<String> currentIds = new HashSet<String>(cursor.getCount());                                 
 643         try {                                                                                            
 644             cursor.moveToPosition(-1);                                                                   
 645             while(cursor.moveToNext()) {                                                                 
 646                 final long id = cursor.getLong(ID_INDEX);                                                
 647                 final String providerName = cursor.getString(APPWIDGET_PROVIDER_INDEX);                  
 648                 final int spanX = cursor.getInt(SPANX_INDEX);                                            
 649                 final int spanY = cursor.getInt(SPANY_INDEX);                                            
 650                 final ComponentName provider = ComponentName.unflattenFromString(providerName);          
 651                 Key key = null;                                                                          
 652                 String backupKey = null;                                                                 
 653                 if (provider != null) {                                                                  
 654                     key = getKey(Key.WIDGET, providerName);                                              
 655                     backupKey = keyToBackupKey(key);                                                     
 656                     currentIds.add(backupKey);                                                           
 657                 } else {                                                                                 
 658                     Log.w(TAG, "empty intent on appwidget: " + id);                                      
 659                 }                                                                                        
 660                 if (savedIds.contains(backupKey)) {                                                      
 661                     if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "already saved widget " + backupKey);                        
 662                                                                                                          
 663                     // remember that we already backed this up previously                                
 664                     keys.add(key);                                                                       
 665                 } else if (backupKey != null) {                                                          
 666                     if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "I can count this high: " + out.rows);                         
 667                     if ((out.rows - startRows) < MAX_WIDGETS_PER_PASS) {                                 
 668                         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "saving widget " + backupKey);                           
 669                         previewLoader.setPreviewSize(spanX * profile.cellWidthPx,                        
 670                                 spanY * profile.cellHeightPx, widgetSpacingLayout);                      
 671                         byte[] blob = packWidget(dpi, previewLoader, mIconCache, provider);              
 672                         keys.add(key);                                                                   
 673                         writeRowToBackup(key, blob, out, data);                                          
 674                                                                                                          
 675                     } else {                                                                             
 676                         if (VERBOSE) Log.d(TAG, "deferring widget backup " + backupKey);                 
 677                         // too many widgets for this pass, request another.                              
 678                         dataChanged();                                                                   
 679                     }                                                                                    
 680                 }                                                                                        
 681             }                                                                                            
 682         } finally {                                                                                      
 683             cursor.close();                                                                              
 684         }                                                                                                
 685         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "widget currentIds.size()=" + currentIds.size());                          
 686                                                                                                          
 687         // these IDs must have been deleted                                                              
 688         savedIds.removeAll(currentIds);                                                                  
 689         out.rows += removeDeletedKeysFromBackup(savedIds, data);                                         
 690     }

 692     /**                                                                                                  
 693      * Read a widget from the stream.                                                                    
 694      *                                                                                                   
 695      * <P>Keys arrive in any order, so widgets that use this data may already exist.                     
 696      *                                                                                                   
 697      * @param key identifier for the row                                                                 
 698      * @param buffer the serialized proto from the stream, may be larger than dataSize                   
 699      * @param dataSize the size of the proto from the stream                                             
 700      * @param keys keys to mark as clean in the notes for next backup                                    
 701      */                                                                                                  
 702     private void restoreWidget(Key key, byte[] buffer, int dataSize, ArrayList<Key> keys) {              
 703         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "unpacking widget " + key.id);                                           
 704         if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "read (" + buffer.length + "): " +                                         
 705                 Base64.encodeToString(buffer, 0, dataSize, Base64.NO_WRAP));                             
 706         try {                                                                                            
 707             Widget widget = unpackWidget(buffer, 0, dataSize);                                           
 708             if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "unpacked " + widget.provider);                                        
 709             if (widget.icon.data != null)  {                                                             
 710                 Bitmap icon = BitmapFactory                                                              
 711                         .decodeByteArray(widget.icon.data, 0, widget.icon.data.length);                  
 712                 if (icon == null) {                                                                      
 713                     Log.w(TAG, "failed to unpack widget icon for " + key.name);                          
 714                 } else {                                                                                 
 715                     IconCache.preloadIcon(mContext, ComponentName.unflattenFromString(widget.provider),  
 716                             icon, widget.icon.dpi);                                                      
 717                 }                                                                                        
 718             }                                                                                            
 719                                                                                                          
 720             if (!mRestoreEnabled) {                                                                      
 721                 if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "restore not enabled: skipping database mutation");              
 722                 return;                                                                                  
 723             } else {                                                                                     
 724                 // future site of widget table mutation                                                  
 725             }                                                                                            
 726         } catch (InvalidProtocolBufferNanoException e) {                                                 
 727             Log.e(TAG, "failed to decode widget", e);                                                    
 728         }                                                                                                
 729     }

 731     /** create a new key, with an integer ID.                                                            
 732      *                                                                                                   
 733      * <P> Keys contain their own checksum instead of using                                              
 734      * the heavy-weight CheckedMessage wrapper.                                                          
 735      */                                                                                                  
 736     private Key getKey(int type, long id) {                                                              
 737         Key key = new Key();                                                                             
 738         key.type = type;                                                                                 
 739         key.id = id;                                                                                     
 740         key.checksum = checkKey(key);                                                                    
 741         return key;                                                                                      
 742     }                                                                                                    
 743                                                                                                          
 744     /** create a new key for a named object.                                                             
 745      *                                                                                                   
 746      * <P> Keys contain their own checksum instead of using                                              
 747      * the heavy-weight CheckedMessage wrapper.                                                          
 748      */                                                                                                  
 749     private Key getKey(int type, String name) {                                                          
 750         Key key = new Key();                                                                             
 751         key.type = type;                                                                                 
 752         key.name = name;                                                                                 
 753         key.checksum = checkKey(key);                                                                    
 754         return key;                                                                                      
 755     }                                                                                                    
 756                                                                                                          
 757     /** keys need to be strings, serialize and encode. */                                                
 758     private String keyToBackupKey(Key key) {                                                             
 759         return Base64.encodeToString(Key.toByteArray(key), Base64.NO_WRAP);                              
 760     }                                                                                                    
 761                                                                                                          
 762     /** keys need to be strings, decode and parse. */                                                    
 763     private Key backupKeyToKey(String backupKey) throws KeyParsingException {                            
 764         try {                                                                                            
 765             Key key = Key.parseFrom(Base64.decode(backupKey, Base64.DEFAULT));                           
 766             if (key.checksum != checkKey(key)) {                                                         
 767                 key = null;                                                                              
 768                 throw new KeyParsingException("invalid key read from stream" + backupKey);               
 769             }                                                                                            
 770             return key;                                                                                  
 771         } catch (InvalidProtocolBufferNanoException e) {                                                 
 772             throw new KeyParsingException(e);                                                            
 773         } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {                                                           
 774             throw new KeyParsingException(e);                                                            
 775         }                                                                                                
 776     }

 778     private String getKeyName(Key key) {                                                                 
 779         if (TextUtils.isEmpty(key.name)) {                                                               
 780             return Long.toString(key.id);                                                                
 781         } else {                                                                                         
 782             return key.name;                                                                             
 783         }                                                                                                
 784                                                                                                          
 785     }

 787     private String geKeyType(Key key) {                                                                  
 788         switch (key.type) {                                                                              
 789             case Key.FAVORITE:                                                                           
 790                 return "favorite";                                                                       
 791             case Key.SCREEN:                                                                             
 792                 return "screen";                                                                         
 793             case Key.ICON:                                                                               
 794                 return "icon";                                                                           
 795             case Key.WIDGET:                                                                             
 796                 return "widget";                                                                         
 797             default:                                                                                     
 798                 return "anonymous";                                                                      
 799         }                                                                                                
 800     }

 802     /** Compute the checksum over the important bits of a key. */                                        
 803     private long checkKey(Key key) {                                                                     
 804         CRC32 checksum = new CRC32();                                                                    
 805         checksum.update(key.type);                                                                       
 806         checksum.update((int) (key.id & 0xffff));                                                        
 807         checksum.update((int) ((key.id >> 32) & 0xffff));                                                
 808         if (!TextUtils.isEmpty(key.name)) {                                                              
 809             checksum.update(key.name.getBytes());                                                        
 810         }                                                                                                
 811         return checksum.getValue();                                                                      
 812     }

 814     /** Serialize a Favorite for persistence, including a checksum wrapper. */                           
 815     private byte[] packFavorite(Cursor c) {                                                              
 816         Favorite favorite = new Favorite();                                                              
 817         favorite.id = c.getLong(ID_INDEX);                                                               
 818         favorite.screen = c.getInt(SCREEN_INDEX);                                                        
 819         favorite.container = c.getInt(CONTAINER_INDEX);                                                  
 820         favorite.cellX = c.getInt(CELLX_INDEX);                                                          
 821         favorite.cellY = c.getInt(CELLY_INDEX);                                                          
 822         favorite.spanX = c.getInt(SPANX_INDEX);                                                          
 823         favorite.spanY = c.getInt(SPANY_INDEX);                                                          
 824         favorite.iconType = c.getInt(ICON_TYPE_INDEX);                                                   
 825         if (favorite.iconType == Favorites.ICON_TYPE_RESOURCE) {                                         
 826             String iconPackage = c.getString(ICON_PACKAGE_INDEX);                                        
 827             if (!TextUtils.isEmpty(iconPackage)) {                                                       
 828                 favorite.iconPackage = iconPackage;                                                      
 829             }                                                                                            
 830             String iconResource = c.getString(ICON_RESOURCE_INDEX);                                      
 831             if (!TextUtils.isEmpty(iconResource)) {                                                      
 832                 favorite.iconResource = iconResource;                                                    
 833             }                                                                                            
 834         }                                                                                                
 835         if (favorite.iconType == Favorites.ICON_TYPE_BITMAP) {                                           
 836             byte[] blob = c.getBlob(ICON_INDEX);                                                         
 837             if (blob != null && blob.length > 0) {                                                       
 838                 favorite.icon = blob;                                                                    
 839             }                                                                                            
 840         }                                                                                                
 841         String title = c.getString(TITLE_INDEX);                                                         
 842         if (!TextUtils.isEmpty(title)) {                                                                 
 843             favorite.title = title;                                                                      
 844         }                                                                                                
 845         String intentDescription = c.getString(INTENT_INDEX);                                            
 846         if (!TextUtils.isEmpty(intentDescription)) {                                                     
 847             try {                                                                                        
 848                 Intent intent = Intent.parseUri(intentDescription, 0);                                   
 849                 intent.removeExtra(ItemInfo.EXTRA_PROFILE);                                              
 850                 favorite.intent = intent.toUri(0);                                                       
 851             } catch (URISyntaxException e) {                                                             
 852                 Log.e(TAG, "Invalid intent", e);                                                         
 853            }                                                                                             
 854         }                                                                                                
 855         favorite.itemType = c.getInt(ITEM_TYPE_INDEX);                                                   
 856         if (favorite.itemType == Favorites.ITEM_TYPE_APPWIDGET) {                                        
 857             favorite.appWidgetId = c.getInt(APPWIDGET_ID_INDEX);                                         
 858             String appWidgetProvider = c.getString(APPWIDGET_PROVIDER_INDEX);                            
 859             if (!TextUtils.isEmpty(appWidgetProvider)) {                                                 
 860                 favorite.appWidgetProvider = appWidgetProvider;                                          
 861             }                                                                                            
 862         }                                                                                                
 863                                                                                                          
 864         return writeCheckedBytes(favorite);                                                              
 865     }

 867     /** Deserialize a Favorite from persistence, after verifying checksum wrapper. */                    
 868     private ContentValues unpackFavorite(byte[] buffer, int offset, int dataSize)                        
 869             throws InvalidProtocolBufferNanoException {                                                  
 870         Favorite favorite = new Favorite();                                                              
 871         MessageNano.mergeFrom(favorite, readCheckedBytes(buffer, offset, dataSize));                     
 872         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "unpacked favorite " + favorite.itemType + ", " +                        
 873                 (TextUtils.isEmpty(favorite.title) ? favorite.id : favorite.title));                     
 874         ContentValues values = new ContentValues();                                                      
 875         values.put(Favorites._ID, favorite.id);                                                          
 876         values.put(Favorites.SCREEN, favorite.screen);                                                   
 877         values.put(Favorites.CONTAINER, favorite.container);                                             
 878         values.put(Favorites.CELLX, favorite.cellX);                                                     
 879         values.put(Favorites.CELLY, favorite.cellY);                                                     
 880         values.put(Favorites.SPANX, favorite.spanX);                                                     
 881         values.put(Favorites.SPANY, favorite.spanY);                                                     
 882         values.put(Favorites.ICON_TYPE, favorite.iconType);                                              
 883         if (favorite.iconType == Favorites.ICON_TYPE_RESOURCE) {                                         
 884             values.put(Favorites.ICON_PACKAGE, favorite.iconPackage);                                    
 885             values.put(Favorites.ICON_RESOURCE, favorite.iconResource);                                  
 886         }                                                                                                
 887         if (favorite.iconType == Favorites.ICON_TYPE_BITMAP) {                                           
 888             values.put(Favorites.ICON, favorite.icon);                                                   
 889         }                                                                                                
 890         if (!TextUtils.isEmpty(favorite.title)) {                                                        
 891             values.put(Favorites.TITLE, favorite.title);                                                 
 892         } else {                                                                                         
 893             values.put(Favorites.TITLE, "");                                                             
 894         }                                                                                                
 895         if (!TextUtils.isEmpty(favorite.intent)) {                                                       
 896             values.put(Favorites.INTENT, favorite.intent);                                               
 897         }                                                                                                
 898         values.put(Favorites.ITEM_TYPE, favorite.itemType);                                              
 899                                                                                                          
 900         UserHandleCompat myUserHandle = UserHandleCompat.myUserHandle();                                 
 901         long userSerialNumber =                                                                          
 902                 UserManagerCompat.getInstance(mContext).getSerialNumberForUser(myUserHandle);            
 903         values.put(LauncherSettings.Favorites.PROFILE_ID, userSerialNumber);                             
 904                                                                                                          
 905         if (favorite.itemType == Favorites.ITEM_TYPE_APPWIDGET) {                                        
 906             if (!TextUtils.isEmpty(favorite.appWidgetProvider)) {                                        
 907                 values.put(Favorites.APPWIDGET_PROVIDER, favorite.appWidgetProvider);                    
 908             }                                                                                            
 909             values.put(Favorites.APPWIDGET_ID, favorite.appWidgetId);                                    
 910             values.put(LauncherSettings.Favorites.RESTORED,                                              
 911                     LauncherAppWidgetInfo.FLAG_ID_NOT_VALID |                                            
 912                     LauncherAppWidgetInfo.FLAG_PROVIDER_NOT_READY |                                      
 913                     LauncherAppWidgetInfo.FLAG_UI_NOT_READY);                                            
 914         } else {                                                                                         
 915             // Let LauncherModel know we've been here.                                                   
 916             values.put(LauncherSettings.Favorites.RESTORED, 1);                                          
 917         }                                                                                                
 918                                                                                                          
 919         return values;                                                                                   
 920     }

 924         Screen screen = new Screen();                                                                    
 925         screen.id = c.getLong(ID_INDEX);                                                                 
 926         screen.rank = c.getInt(SCREEN_RANK_INDEX);                                                       
 927                                                                                                          
 928         return writeCheckedBytes(screen);                                                                
 929     }

 931     /** Deserialize a Screen from persistence, after verifying checksum wrapper. */                      
 932     private ContentValues unpackScreen(byte[] buffer, int offset, int dataSize)                          
 933             throws InvalidProtocolBufferNanoException {                                                  
 934         Screen screen = new Screen();                                                                    
 935         MessageNano.mergeFrom(screen, readCheckedBytes(buffer, offset, dataSize));                       
 936         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "unpacked screen " + screen.id + "/" + screen.rank);                     
 937         ContentValues values = new ContentValues();                                                      
 938         values.put(WorkspaceScreens._ID, screen.id);                                                     
 939         values.put(WorkspaceScreens.SCREEN_RANK, screen.rank);                                           
 940         return values;                                                                                   
 941     }

 943     /** Serialize an icon Resource for persistence, including a checksum wrapper. */                     
 944     private byte[] packIcon(int dpi, Bitmap icon) {                                                      
 945         Resource res = new Resource();                                                                   
 946         res.dpi = dpi;                                                                                   
 947         ByteArrayOutputStream os = new ByteArrayOutputStream();                                          
 948         if (icon.compress(IMAGE_FORMAT, IMAGE_COMPRESSION_QUALITY, os)) {                                
 949             res.data = os.toByteArray();                                                                 
 950         }                                                                                                
 951         return writeCheckedBytes(res);                                                                   
 952     }

 954     /** Deserialize an icon resource from persistence, after verifying checksum wrapper. */              
 955     private static Resource unpackIcon(byte[] buffer, int offset, int dataSize)                          
 956             throws InvalidProtocolBufferNanoException {                                                  
 957         Resource res = new Resource();                                                                   
 958         MessageNano.mergeFrom(res, readCheckedBytes(buffer, offset, dataSize));                          
 959         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "unpacked icon " + res.dpi + "/" + res.data.length);                     
 960         return res;                                                                                      
 961     }                                                                                                    
 962                                                                                                          
 963     /** Serialize a widget for persistence, including a checksum wrapper. */                             
 964     private byte[] packWidget(int dpi, WidgetPreviewLoader previewLoader, IconCache iconCache,           
 965             ComponentName provider) {                                                                    
 966         final AppWidgetProviderInfo info = findAppWidgetProviderInfo(provider);                          
 967         Widget widget = new Widget();                                                                    
 968         widget.provider = provider.flattenToShortString();                                               
 969         widget.label = info.label;                                                                       
 970         widget.configure = info.configure != null;                                                       
 971         if (info.icon != 0) {                                                                            
 972             widget.icon = new Resource();                                                                
 973             Drawable fullResIcon = iconCache.getFullResIcon(provider.getPackageName(), info.icon);       
 974             Bitmap icon = Utilities.createIconBitmap(fullResIcon, mContext);                             
 975             ByteArrayOutputStream os = new ByteArrayOutputStream();                                      
 976             if (icon.compress(IMAGE_FORMAT, IMAGE_COMPRESSION_QUALITY, os)) {                            
 977                 widget.icon.data = os.toByteArray();                                                     
 978                 widget.icon.dpi = dpi;                                                                   
 979             }                                                                                            
 980         }                                                                                                
 981         if (info.previewImage != 0) {                                                                    
 982             widget.preview = new Resource();                                                             
 983             Bitmap preview = previewLoader.generateWidgetPreview(info, null);                            
 984             ByteArrayOutputStream os = new ByteArrayOutputStream();                                      
 985             if (preview.compress(IMAGE_FORMAT, IMAGE_COMPRESSION_QUALITY, os)) {                         
 986                 widget.preview.data = os.toByteArray();                                                  
 987                 widget.preview.dpi = dpi;                                                                
 988             }                                                                                            
 989         }                                                                                                
 990         return writeCheckedBytes(widget);                                                                
 991     }                                                                                                    
 992                                                                                                          
 993     /** Deserialize a widget from persistence, after verifying checksum wrapper. */                      
 994     private Widget unpackWidget(byte[] buffer, int offset, int dataSize)                                 
 995             throws InvalidProtocolBufferNanoException {                                                  
 996         Widget widget = new Widget();                                                                    
 997         MessageNano.mergeFrom(widget, readCheckedBytes(buffer, offset, dataSize));                       
 998         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "unpacked widget " + widget.provider);                                   
 999         return widget;                                                                                   
1000     }                                                                                                    
1001                                                                                                          
1002     /**                                                                                                  
1003      * Read the old journal from the input file.                                                         
1004      *                                                                                                   
1005      * In the event of any error, just pretend we didn't have a journal,                                 
1006      * in that case, do a full backup.                                                                   
1007      *                                                                                                   
1008      * @param oldState the read-0only file descriptor pointing to the old journal                        
1009      * @return a Journal protocol buffer                                                                 
1010      */                                                                                                  
1011     private Journal readJournal(ParcelFileDescriptor oldState) {                                         
1012         Journal journal = new Journal();                                                                 
1013         if (oldState == null) {                                                                          
1014             return journal;                                                                              
1015         }                                                                                                
1016         FileInputStream inStream = new FileInputStream(oldState.getFileDescriptor());                    
1017         try {                                                                                            
1018             int availableBytes = inStream.available();                                                   
1019             if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "available " + availableBytes);                                        
1020             if (availableBytes < MAX_JOURNAL_SIZE) {                                                     
1021                 byte[] buffer = new byte[availableBytes];                                                
1022                 int bytesRead = 0;                                                                       
1023                 boolean valid = false;                                                                   
1024                 InvalidProtocolBufferNanoException lastProtoException = null;                            
1025                 while (availableBytes > 0) {                                                             
1026                     try {                                                                                
1027                         // OMG what are you doing? This is crazy inefficient!                            
1028                         // If we read a byte that is not ours, we will cause trouble: b/12491813         
1029                         // However, we don't know how many bytes to expect (oops).                       
1030                         // So we have to step through *slowly*, watching for the end.                    
1031                         int result = inStream.read(buffer, bytesRead, 1);                                
1032                         if (result > 0) {                                                                
1033                             availableBytes -= result;                                                    
1034                             bytesRead += result;                                                         
1035                             if (DEBUG && (bytesRead % 100 == 0)) {                                       
1036                                 Log.d(TAG, "read some bytes: " + bytesRead);                             
1037                             }                                                                            
1038                         } else {                                                                         
1039                             Log.w(TAG, "unexpected end of file while reading journal.");                 
1040                             // stop reading and see what there is to parse                               
1041                             availableBytes = 0;                                                          
1042                         }                                                                                
1043                     } catch (IOException e) {                                                            
1044                         buffer = null;                                                                   
1045                         availableBytes = 0;                                                              
1046                     }                                                                                    
1047                                                                                                          
1048                     // check the buffer to see if we have a valid journal                                
1049                     try {                                                                                
1050                         MessageNano.mergeFrom(journal, readCheckedBytes(buffer, 0, bytesRead));          
1051                         // if we are here, then we have read a valid, checksum-verified journal          
1052                         valid = true;                                                                    
1053                         availableBytes = 0;                                                              
1054                         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "read " + bytesRead + " bytes of journal");              
1055                     } catch (InvalidProtocolBufferNanoException e) {                                     
1056                         // if we don't have the whole journal yet, mergeFrom will throw. keep going.     
1057                         lastProtoException = e;                                                          
1058                         journal.clear();                                                                 
1059                     }                                                                                    
1060                 }                                                                                        
1061                 if (DEBUG) Log.d(TAG, "journal bytes read: " + bytesRead);                               
1062                 if (!valid) {                                                                            
1063                     Log.w(TAG, "could not find a valid journal", lastProtoException);                    
1064                 }                                                                                        
1065             }                                                                                            
1066         } catch (IOException e) {                                                                        
1067             Log.w(TAG, "failed to close the journal", e);                                                
1068         } finally {                                                                                      
1069             try {                                                                                        
1070                 inStream.close();                                                                        
1071             } catch (IOException e) {                                                                    
1072                 Log.w(TAG, "failed to close the journal", e);                                            
1073             }                                                                                            
1074         }                                                                                                
1075         return journal;                                                                                  
1076     }                                                                                                    
1077                                                                                                          
1078     private void writeRowToBackup(Key key, byte[] blob, Journal out,                                     
1079             BackupDataOutput data) throws IOException {                                                  
1080         String backupKey = keyToBackupKey(key);                                                          
1081         data.writeEntityHeader(backupKey, blob.length);                                                  
1082         data.writeEntityData(blob, blob.length);                                                         
1083         out.rows++;                                                                                      
1084         out.bytes += blob.length;                                                                        
1085         if (VERBOSE) Log.v(TAG, "saving " + geKeyType(key) + " " + backupKey + ": " +                    
1086                 getKeyName(key) + "/" + blob.length);                                                    
1087         if(DEBUG_PAYLOAD) {                                                                              
1088             String encoded = Base64.encodeToString(blob, 0, blob.length, Base64.NO_WRAP);                
1089             final int chunkSize = 1024;                                                                  
1090             for (int offset = 0; offset < encoded.length(); offset += chunkSize) {                       
1091                 int end = offset + chunkSize;                                                            
1092                 end = Math.min(end, encoded.length());                                                   
1093                 Log.w(TAG, "wrote " + encoded.substring(offset, end));                                   
1094             }                                                                                            
1095         }                                                                                                
1096     }
